Discussions
-----------

There is no way to simply monitor data access pattern

DAMON provides monitoring results that fine-grained for memory
management.  For basic observability, though, it is too much
information.  The control is also arguably too complicated.  Introduce a
static kernel module that can easily be enabled and used.

The module makes its usage simple by providing parameter for turning it
on, which can be set at boot time.  The module uses monitoring intervals
auto-tuning to make it just works while consuming only minimum sytem
resource.

The module defines two simple access pattern metrics, namely page
idletime percentiles and estimated memory bandwidth.

